nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py.message:
@Matt, this is just excluding based on the type of disk due to special handling earlier.

The original code assumes it's a file path, which would have a basename of 'disk.swap' here. However, for LVM the basename of the logical volume (a block device) is '/dev/<vg>/<instance_uuid>_disk.swap', so fname here is <instance_uuid>_disk.swap. As I commented it would be much nicer to have the imagebackend parse this for us and do an == comparison, but it's not worth the code motion to make that happen imho. This code needs to die anyway.

Note this this code would also be problematic for rbd, but rbd disks don't get here because in libvirt they don't have a path element, and are excluded earlier by _get_instance_disk_info_from_config().

